sentences: Martin K. Bracey (born September 17, 1954, in Chicago, Illinois), known as Marty Bracey, is an American drummer and percussionist mostly known for being in many Japanese bands.
He came to Japan in 1973, making his professional debut in Japan in 1978.

In 1987, he was hired as a drummer for the Japanese band 1986 Omega Tribe, helping with the band during their rename to Carlos Toshiki & Omega Tribe and their debut album.
